&lt;p&gt;In addition to structs and methods, Go also supports several other OOP concepts, including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Polymorphism:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go supports polymorphism through the use of interfaces. An interface defines a set of methods that can be implemented by any type. A type that implements an interface is said to be polymorphic with respect to that interface.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here’s an example of how to define and implement an interface in Go:&lt;/p&gt;
